21. DEJA DUP
-------------------------------------------------

# GUI backup utility (GNOME)
deja-dup

# Features
- Full and incremental backups
- Scheduled automatic backups
- Encryption (via duplicity)
- Local, network, and cloud storage
- Easy restore through GUI

# Common backup destinations
- Local Folder
- External Drive
- Network Share
- Google Drive
- Other supported cloud providers

-------------------------------------------------
22. DUPLICITY
-------------------------------------------------

# Full backup
duplicity /home/user file:///backup

# Encrypted backup (GPG)
duplicity --encrypt-key <GPG_KEY_ID> /home/user file:///backup

# Restore latest backup
duplicity restore file:///backup /restore

# Restore specific file
duplicity restore \
--file-to-restore Documents/report.pdf \
file:///backup /restore/report.pdf

# Incremental backup
duplicity incr /home/user file:///backup

# Verify backup
duplicity verify file:///backup /home/user

# List backup files
duplicity collection-status file:///backup

# Remove backups older than 30 days
duplicity remove-older-than 30D file:///backup

# Common backend examples
file:///backup
scp://user@host//backup
sftp://user@host//backup
ftp://user@host/backup

-------------------------------------------------
23. DEJA DUP vs DUPLICITY
-------------------------------------------------

Deja Dup   → GUI frontend
Duplicity  → Command-line backup engine

Deja Dup internally uses Duplicity to create encrypted,
compressed, incremental backups.
